title: Moray
summary: Moray (/ˈmʌreɪ/ MURR-ay; Scots: Moray; Scottish Gaelic: Moireibh or Moireabh) is one of the 32 local government council areas of Scotland. It lies in the north-east of the country, with a coastline on the Moray Firth, and borders the council areas of Aberdeenshire and Highland.
